                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72112/1258½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss> ad interim</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">14 June, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I think that this despatch<note
                        n="79" xml:id="d257fn1">Draft telegram, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>
                    ought to be sent. Every word of it is true.</p>
                <p>But Colonel House, who comes direct from London, landed in New York yesterday
                    from the <hi rend="italic">Saint Paul;</hi> and, if a delay of a day or two
                    would not be imprudent, I think we had better wait to get his advice. He is well
                    informed, I happen to know on these very matters and has himself been advising
                    the British Foreign Office of our attitude.</p>
                <p>Cordially Yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. W.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
